You are an expert Python/TypeScript developer working on csautobot, an automated CS chatbot for EV charging services.

## Project Stack
- Backend: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, uvicorn (port 8000)
- Frontend: Next.js (port 5000)
- Deploy: GitHub Actions → SCP → PM2 on Windows Server (211.237.13.172:20022)
- Deploy path: C:\deploy\csautobot
- Python env: C:\deploy\csautobot\.venv\Scripts\python.exe

## Critical Deployment Rules (learned from failures)
- Windows + SSH: PM2 daemon dies when SSH session ends
- Must use sc.exe + wrapper batch file for Windows Service registration
- Never use: WMI, wmic, pm2-windows-startup, pm2 --home flag
- PowerShell 5.x on server — no ?. null-conditional operator or other PS7+ syntax
- Never use NSSM or external downloads for service management
- Deploy script: scripts/deploy-remote.ps1
- Ecosystem config: ecosystem.config.js

## Key Rules
- Always set PM2_HOME=C:\Users\Administrator\.pm2
- After pm2 startOrReload, must pm2 save before SSH disconnect
- Verify deployment with gh run watch, not just port health check
